tes":"Multiple town offices per Stiles book"},{"role":"State Representative","organization":"Connecticut General Assembly","location":"Hartford, Connecticut","start_year":1854,"end_year":1885,"notes":"Lower House 1854, 1884, 1885 (3 sessions)."},{"role":"Vestryman / Warden","organization":"St. John's Episcopal Church, North Haven","location":"North Haven, Connecticut","end_year":1895,"notes":"Per Stiles book #950."}],"military_service":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"artworks":[],"tags":["cousin_marriage","state_representative"],"research_tags":[],"cross_connections":[],"narrative_blocks":[{"number":1,"category":"politics","header":"He returned to the legislature after thirty years","body":"A New Haven brickmaker and church warden who filled nearly every town office, he sat in the Connecticut house in 1854 — then again in 1884 and 1885, three decades later. He led the firm I. L. Stiles & Son into his late sixties."},{"number":2,"category":"marriage","header":"He married a Hooker cousin without the name","body":"His first wife, Sophronia Blakeslee, turned out to descend from the same Stiles-Hooker root he did, through a different daughter — a cousin match neither surname revealed."}],"quotes":[],"sources":[{"label":"Stiles book (BIB008) #950/#603"},{"label":"FindAGrave 126791136","url":"https://www.findagrave.com/memorial/126791136/isaac_lorenzo-stiles"}],"research_sources":[{"bib_id":"BIB008"}],"documents":[],"slug":"isaac-stiles-1819"},"HD3948":{"id":"HD3948","former_ids":["I00525"],"is_placeholder":false,"has_descendants_documented":true,"bio":{"first_name":"Sophronia","middle_name":"Maria","last_name":"Stiles","maiden_name":"Blakeslee","married_names":["Stiles"],"gender":"female","display_name":"Sophronia Maria Blakeslee Stiles","bio_blurb":"New Haven bride of a Hooker cousin"},"birth":{"year":1819,"month":2,"day":16,"city":"North Haven","county":"New Haven","state":"Connecticut","country":"United States"},"baptism":{},"death":{"year":1886,"month":11,"day":17,"city":"North Haven","county":"New Haven","state":"Connecticut","country":"United States"},"residence":{},"burial":{"cemetery_id":"CEM293"},"classification":{"is_thomas_descendant":true,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_thomas_spouse":false,"is_talcott_spouse":false,"generation_from_thomas":8,"include_in_path_calculation":true,"descent_paths_to_thomas":1,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":true,"is_progenitor":false,"is_easter_egg":false},"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"parents":{"father_id":"I00531","mother_id":"H01162","father_research_notes":"Daughter of Anson Blakeslee + Julia (Frost) Blakeslee. Per Stiles book #950: 'Julia, dau of Titus and Mabel Frost' — Julia IS our existing H01162 Julia Frost Blakeslee! Sophronia is herself gen 7 Hooker descendant via H01162 → H00448 Mabel Stiles Frost branch. Marriage to Isaac Lorenzo Stiles (HD3934, gen 7 via Mary Stiles H00452 branch) is a Hooker-Hooker cousin marriage between two different branches of Esther Hooker → Rev. Isaac Stiles. Sophronia will be RECLASSIFIED to HD-prefix in Stage 6Y-43 after H01162 Julia is enriched with full child list. Built here as I-spouse with cousin_marriage tag."},"number_of_marriages":1,"marriages":[{"marriage_number":1,"spouse_id":"HD3934","date_year":1842,"date_month":2,"date_day":16,"location_city":"North Haven","location_state":"Connecticut","location_country":"United States","end_type":"death","end_year":1886,"children_ids":["HD3938","HD3939"]}],"education":[],"career":[],"military_service":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"artworks":[],"tags":["cousin_marriage"],"research_tags":[],"cross_connections":[],"narrative_blocks":[{"number":1,"category":"marriage","header":"Wed Isaac Lorenzo on her 23rd birthday, 1842","body":"Sophronia Maria Blakeslee was born February 16, 1819 in North Haven Connecticut; on her 23rd birthday — February 16, 1842 — she married Isaac Lorenzo Stiles in the same town. Their union joined two branches of Esther Hooker's descendants: Sophronia descended through the Mabel Stiles Frost line, Isaac Lorenzo through the Mary Stiles Mansfield line."},{"number":2,"category":"marriage","header":"She married on her twenty-third birthday","body":"On February 16, 1842 — her birthday — she wed Isaac Lorenzo Stiles, born the same year as she. The match joined two branches of the Esther Hooker line, a cousin marriage that doubled their sons’ descent."}],"quotes":[],"sources":[{"label":"FindAGrave 126791203","url":"https://www.findagrave.com/memorial/126791203/sophronia_maria-stiles"}],"research_sources":[{"bib_id":"BIB008"}],"documents":[],"slug":"sophronia-stiles-1819"},"H01182":{"id":"H01182","former_ids":["HD3922"],"is_placeholder":false,"has_descendants_documented":true,"bio":{"first_name":"Isaac","last_name":"Stiles","married_names":[],"gender":"male","display_name":"Isaac Stiles"},"birth":{"year":1792,"month":8,"day":2,"city":"North Haven","county":"New Haven","state":"Connecticut","country":"United States"},"baptism":{},"death":{"year":1842,"month":2,"day":4,"city":"North Haven","county":"New Haven","state":"Connecticut","country":"United States"},"residence":{"city":"North Haven","county":"New Haven","state":"Connecticut","country":"United States"},"burial":{"cemetery_id":"CEM293"},"classification":{"is_thomas_descendant":true,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_thomas_spouse":false,"is_talcott_spouse":false,"generation_from_thomas":7,"include_in_path_calculation":true,"descent_paths_to_thomas":1,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":true,"is_progenitor":false,"is_easter_egg":false},"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"parents":{"father_id":"H00454","father_name":"Capt. Isaac Clark Stiles","mother_id":"X01370","mother_name":"Eunice Blakeslee"},"number_of_marriages":1,"marriages":[{"marriage_number":1,"spouse_id":"I00524","date_year":1815,"date_month":11,"date_day":28,"location_city":"North Haven","location_county":"New Haven","location_state":"Connecticut","location_country":"United States","end_type":"death","end_year":1842,"children_ids":["HD3933","HD3923","HD3934","HD3935","HD3936","HD3937"]}],"education":[],"career":[{"role":"Farmer + brick manufacturer","location":"North Haven, Connecticut","end_year":1842,"notes":"Family business — established brick mfg trade that became I. L. Stiles & Son under son Isaac Lorenzo."},{"role":"State Representative","organization":"Connecticut General Assembly","location":"Hartford, Connecticut","start_year":1831,"end_year":1831,"notes":"Represented N. Haven 1831 per Stiles book #601."},{"role":"Justice of the Peace","organization":"Town of North Haven, Connecticut","location":"North Haven, Connecticut","notes":"Per Stiles book #601."},{"role":"Postmaster","organization":"US Postal Service, North Haven, Connecticut","location":"North Haven, Connecticut","notes":"Per Stiles book #601."},{"role":"Warden","organization":"St. John's Episcopal Church, North Haven","location":"North Haven, Connecticut","end_year":1842,"notes":"Many years as Warden per Stiles book #601."}],"military_service":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"artworks":[],"tags":["episcopal","politician","postmaster"],"research_tags":[],"cross_connections":[],"narrative_blocks":[{"number":1,"category":"career","header":"Brickmaker, postmaster, JP, state representative","body":"Isaac Stiles built a multi-role public life in North Haven Connecticut — farmer and brick manufacturer, Justice of the Peace and Postmaster for many years, warden of St. John's Episcopal Church, and representative of North Haven in the Lower House of the Connecticut General Assembly in 1831. He 'held all important town offices' per the Stiles family book — typical of the local-elite figure who structured pre-Civil-War Connecticut town life."},{"number":2,"category":"family","header":"Two young sons died 1832, probable epidemic","body":"Two of Isaac Stiles's documented six children — Edward C. and William H. — both died in 1832. The shared death year strongly suggests an epidemic; 1832 was the year of the first North American cholera pandemic that reached Connecticut. Isaac himself died February 4, 1842 at age forty-nine, leaving widow Lois Cooper Stiles to live until 1872 — thirty years past him."}],"quotes":[],"sources":[],"research_sources":[{"bib_id":"BIB008"}],"documents":[],"slug":"isaac-stiles-1792"},"I00524":{"id":"I00524","former_ids":[],"is_placeholder":false,"has_descendants_documented":true,"bio":{"first_name":"Lois","last_name":"Stiles","maiden_name":"Cooper","married_names":["Stiles"],"gender":"female","display_name":"Lois Cooper Stiles"},"birth":{"year":1792,"month":3,"day":31,"city":"North Haven","county":"New Haven","state":"Connecticut","country":"United States"},"baptism":{},"death":{"year":1872,"month":12,"day":31,"city":"North Haven","county":"New Haven","state":"Connecticut","country":"United States"},"residence":{},"burial":{"cemetery_id":"CEM293"},"classification":{"is_thomas_descendant":false,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_thomas_spouse":true,"is_talcott_spouse":false,"include_in_path_calculation":false,"descent_paths_to_thomas":0,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":false,"is_progenitor":false,"is_easter_egg":false},"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"parents":{"father_research_notes":"Daughter of Justus and Lois Cooper of North Haven CT. Both non-Hooker, not built."},"number_of_marriages":1,"marriages":[{"marriage_number":1,"spouse_id":"H01182","date_year":1815,"date_month":11,"date_day":28,"location_city":"North Haven","location_state":"Connecticut","location_country":"United States","end_type":"death_of_spouse","end_year":1842,"children_ids":["HD3933","HD3923","HD3934","HD3935","HD3936","HD3937"]}],"education":[],"career":[],"military_service":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"artworks":[],"tags":[],"research_tags":[],"cross_connections":[],"narrative_blocks":[],"quotes":[],"sources":[{"label":"FindAGrave 127196647","